tissueExpression.summary: General cytoplasmic and membranous expression. Detected at High or Medium expression levels in 50 of 81 analyzed normal tissue cell types.

Distinct staining was observed in connective tissue. Heart muscle displayed strong cytoplasmic positivity. Moderate nuclear and/or cytoplasmic positivity was observed in respiratory epithelia, Purkinje cells, neuronal cells of cerebral cortex, renal tubules, hepatocytes, rectum, salivary gland, smooth muscle cells, stomach, testis and thyroid. Remaining normal tissues were weakly stained or negative.
tissueExpression.validation: Partly consistent with extensive gene/protein characterization data

tissueExpression.summary: Most testicular cancers along with several melanomas, gliomas, urothelial, colorectal, prostate, ovarian and cervical cancers displayed moderate nuclear positivity. Remaining cancer tissues were mainly negative.

tissueExpression.summary: Most normal tissues showed moderate to strong cytoplasmic and membranous positivity. Squamous epithelium, prostatic glands and soft tissues were weakly stained or negative.
tissueExpression.validation: Partly consistent with gene/protein characterization data

tissueExpression.summary: Cancer tissues showed weak to moderate cytoplasmic and membranous positivity. A few liver and colorectal cancers exhibited strong immunoreactivity. Several gliomas, carcinoids, lung, cervical, urothelia, prostate and renal cancers were weakly stained or negative.
